----------
01.06.2020
----------

* trde_twitter.whole.simp_orig_norm.giza_man.algn	

token-level 1:1, 1:n, n:1 alignments 
format: <tweet no>\t<orig>\t<norm>

- n:1 representation: 1 is on the first line
13	Bir	Birçok
13	çok	
13	ev	ev

- 1:n representation: n is on a single line, separated by a space
9	napıyorum	ne yapıyorum

- The first token NULL comes from Giza++ aligments, obsolete at the moment.


* trde_twitter.whole.simp_orig_norm.giza_man.algn.lid

gold language IDs assigned to the orig column

format: <tweet no>\t<orig>\t<norm>\t<lid>

NULL lines are removed


* trde_twitter.whole.simp_orig_norm.giza_man.algn.pos

gold POS tags assigned to the orig column

format: <tweet no>\t<orig>\t<norm>\t<pos>

NULL lines are removed

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* The original data comes from 

Özlem Çetinoğlu and Çağrı Çöltekin
Part of Speech Annotation of a Turkish-German Code-Switching Corpus
In the Proceedings of the 10th Linguistic Annotation Workshop (LAW-X), August 2016, Berlin, Germany.

http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/W/W16/W16-1714.pdf


